    <p>Spider-Man is one of the most popular and iconic superheroes in the Marvel Comics universe. He was created by
        writer-editor Stan Lee and artist Steve Ditko, and first appeared in Amazing Fantasy #15 in 19621. Spider-Man’s
        real name is Peter Parker, a shy teenager who lives with his aunt May and uncle Ben in New York City. He gains
        spider-like abilities after being bitten by a radioactive spider during a school field trip to a science lab. He
        decides to use his powers for good after his uncle Ben is killed by a burglar that he failed to stop. He adopts
        the motto “With great power comes great responsibility” as his guiding principle.

        Spider-Man’s abilities include super strength, agility, reflexes, endurance, and speed. He can cling to walls
        and ceilings, and shoot webs from his wrists using devices called web-shooters. He also has a “spider-sense”
        that warns him of danger. He wears a red and blue costume with a spider emblem on his chest and a mask that
