        skilled fighter and inventor, and has a genius-level intellect. He works as a freelance photographer for the
        Daily Bugle, a newspaper that often criticizes him as a menace.

        Spider-Man has faced many foes and challenges throughout his career. Some of his most notable enemies are the
        Green Goblin, Doctor Octopus, Venom, Electro, Sandman, and the Vulture. He has also teamed up with other heroes
        such as the Avengers, the Fantastic Four, and the X-Men. He has had several romantic interests, such as Gwen
        Stacy, Mary Jane Watson, and Black Cat. He has also dealt with personal issues, such as guilt, loss, identity,
        and responsibility. He has sometimes struggled to balance his superhero life with his civilian life, and has
        faced consequences for his actions.

        Spider-Man is widely regarded as one of the most relatable and influential superheroes of all time. He has been
        featured in various media, such as comics, cartoons, movies, video games, and merchandise. He has been portrayed
        by several actors, such as Tobey Maguire, Andrew Garfield, and Tom Holland. He has also been adapted into
        different versions and alternate realities, such as Spider-Man 2099, Spider-Gwen, and Miles Morales. He is a
        cultural icon and a symbol of hope, courage, and heroism.

